  "prompt": "Which banks cooperate with Costa Rica gambling websites?",
  "response": "In Costa Rica, the gambling industry operates under a unique set of regulations, which can make banking relationships complex. While Costa Rica itself does not issue gambling licenses, it allows foreign-licensed gambling companies to operate from its territory. This situation influences the banking options available to these gambling websites.\n\nSome banks that are known to work with Costa Rica-based gambling websites include:\n\n1. **Banco Nacional de Costa Rica**: One of the largest banks in the country, it has been known to handle transactions for gambling operators.\n2. **Banco de Costa Rica**: Another major bank that sometimes works with gambling companies.\n3. **Banco Promerica**: Known for its international connections, it may facilitate transactions for gambling businesses.\n4. **Bcredentials**: A smaller bank that has been reported to work with some gambling operators.\n\nIt's important to note that banking relationships can change, and not all branches or accounts within these banks may be open to dealing with gambling businesses. Additionally, many gambling operators in Costa Rica use offshore banking solutions to manage their finances, often in jurisdictions like Malta, Gibraltar, or Cura\u00e7ao, where gambling regulations are more established.\n\nAlways ensure that any banking relationship complies with local and international regulations. If you're involved in the gambling industry in Costa Rica, consulting with a legal and financial advisor familiar with the sector is highly recommended.",
